post_text: Message from Alden-Hebron Middle School: This Friday, September 4th will be a remote learning half-day for students. Students will be expected to log-in to the 1st hour class 7:40 and their 5th hour class at 10:38 for attendance purposes only. The rest of this time will be asynchronous learning and students are expected to catch up on missing work or complete work that is assigned on Thursday. Teachers will be available to assist students. Please e-mail the teacher if you need assistance. Individual times will be set-up to help students using the office hours link. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact the school office.

post_text: Tonight’s parade route!!! Thank you Hebron-Alden-Greenwood Fire Protection District.
shared_text:
Hebron-Alden-Greenwood Fire Protection District
April 17 at 10:17 PM ·

Tonight the Hebron Alden Greenwood Fire and Hebron Police, in conjunction with Alden Hebron School District #19, are doing a Friday Night Lights Parade throughout #GiantNation tonight starting at 7PM. We will be traveling throughout Hebron and Alden, as well as the football field lights will be turned on, to show support for the healthcare workers and first responders. We also want to show our support and pride for our students. We hope this will give everyone a little boost during these difficult times. We hope this will help you stay positive and #GiantStrong

The maps below show an approximate route that will be taken!

If you do come outside to watch remember to maintain Social Distancing!
text:
Tonight’s parade route!!! Thank you Hebron-Alden-Greenwood Fire Protection District.

post_text:
Due to the continued concerns with the spread of the Corona Virus and out of extreme caution for the safety of our families and students, and following the recommendations of the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) to avoid large gatherings, including the upcoming play and 5th grade living museum, any audience or spectator events, such as concerts, funfairs, STEM nights, sporting events, and school-sponsored events are canceled immediately, until further notice.

School clubs, activities, and sport practices including students and staff only will still be held as of now. .

School clubs, activities, and sport practices including students and staff only will still be held as of now. .

post_text:
Message from Lake County Tech Campus:

The Tech Campus believes the safety of students and staff is our top priority. In our attempt to help contain and mitigate the continued spreading of the virus, the Tech Campus plans to cancel classes and close the campus beginning March 16-March 20. The Tech Campus will be on spring break the following week, March 23-27. We will follow our e-Learning procedures each day of the week. During this time, we will be deep cleaning our entire facility as well as minimizing the chances of a virus transfer from person to person. This action is not a result of any recommendation from the department of health, but I feel that it’s in the best interest of our students, staff, and our communities.
